             sworn. - I am a widow, I live at No. 12, <placeName id="t18010114-62-crimeloc354">Bolsover-street, Oxford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18010114-62-crimeloc354" type="placeName" value="Bolsover-street, Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18010114-62-crimeloc354" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18010114-62-off351 t18010114-62-crimeloc354"></join>, it is a public-house, I lodge at the top of the house; On Monday the 29th of December, about half past four o'clock, I lost the things mentioned in the indictment out of my drawers; I met the prisoner coming down stairs with them, tied up in a silk handkerchief; I had been out about a quarter of an hour; I left my child, about eight years old, in the room; the prisoner passed me on the stairs, and called to a man in the tap-room, of the name of Joe, but there was no such man there; she was then going out at the door, I asked her where the bundle was that she had brought down stairs with<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="180101140077"></xptr>her; she said, she had none; I said, yes, you have a bundle; I turned round, and the bundle sell from under her petticoats; I picked it up, and took her into another room, and searched her; she told me it was not her that had robbed me, there was somebody more up stairs; I called the landlord to go up, but he found nobody; Sarah Baldwin lodges in the same room with me; she came in, and I delivered the prisoner up to her; the officer has the property.(
               <persName id="t18010114-62-person664">
                  William 
                  Jackson
               <interp inst="t18010114-62-person664" type="surname" value="Jackson"></interp>
